==Quest rings==
{{Infotable Bonuses|Lunar ring|Beacon ring|Ring of charos#Normal|'perfect' ring|Ring of visibility|nototals=yes}}
The Ring of charos is used to persuade certain NPCs, allowing discounts. 
The ring of visibility is used to see the normally invisible e.g. ghosts.

==Other rings==
; [[Fremennik rings]]
{{Infotable Bonuses|Warrior ring|Berserker ring|Seers ring|Archers ring|nototals=yes}}

; [[Wilderness rings]]
{{Infotable Bonuses|Treasonous ring|Tyrannical ring|Ring of the gods|nototals=yes}}

; Other rings
{{Infotable Bonuses|Brimstone ring|Explorer's ring 4|Granite ring|Elven signet|Ring of endurance#Uncharged|Hallowed ring|Celestial ring#Uncharged|Ring of the elements#Uncharged|nototals=yes}}
The Hallowed ring negates all direct damage within the [[Hallowed Sepulchre]].
The Elven signet provides a 10% chance to not use charges of [[crystal equipment]].
The Explorer's ring can be used to teleport to the cabbage patch south of Falador.
The Ring of endurance extends the effects of [[stamina potions]] and passively reduces [[Energy|run energy]] drain by 15% when charged with 500 or more doses of [[stamina potion]].
The Celestial ring gives an invisible +4 boost to [[Mining]] and also gives a chance of obtaining an extra ore up to [[Adamantite rock|adamantite]].

==Imbued rings==
Some rings may be imbued with an enchantment as a reward from [[Nightmare Zone]]. Imbuing them doubles their combat bonuses. All rings, excluding the [[ring of suffering]] and [[Granite ring]], cost 650,000 Nightmare Zone points each to upgrade (a [[holy wrench]] is also required to upgrade the ring of the gods). The rings that may be imbued are:

; [[Fremennik rings]]
{{Infotable Bonuses|Warrior ring (i)#Nightmare_Zone|Berserker ring (i)#Nightmare_Zone|Seers ring (i)#Nightmare_Zone|Archers ring (i)#Nightmare_Zone|nototals=yes}}

; [[Wilderness rings]]
{{Infotable Bonuses|Treasonous ring (i)#Nightmare_Zone|Tyrannical ring (i)#Nightmare_Zone|Ring of the gods (i)#Nightmare_Zone|nototals=yes}}

; Other
{{Infotable Bonuses|Ring of suffering (i)#Uncharged|Granite ring (i)#Nightmare_Zone|Ring of wealth (i)#Uncharged|nototals=yes}}
The imbued ring of wealth offers double chance of clue scroll drops in the Wilderness.

==Transformation rings==
These rings offers no bonuses, but allows players to transform to appear as different objects.
